    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The equilibrium mixing calculation assumes symmetric players and the specific 1/5 payoff ratio from Nordstrom. Different payoffs shift the equilibrium probability but the qualitative result holds: more players, lower individual probability of volunteering, and the group failure probability can increase with group size.</p>


    <PrevNext prev={{ href: "/reading/game-theory/nordstrom-12/", label: "Prisoner's Dilemma" }} next={{ href: "/reading/game-theory/nordstrom-14/", label: "Repeated Prisoner's" }} />

  </main>
